  "secText": [
    "  <b class=\"object-name\">Supplemental Material: </b>  <span class=\"object-name\">AP</span>",
    "  <b>Essential Question: </b>  <br />How can we calculate the torque acting on an object?",
    "  <b>Enduring Understandings:</b>  <b>    <br />  </b>1. <a class='pjumpToTopic' href='javascript:void(0)' data-chap='9' data-topic='3' data-subtopic='1' data-subsection='0'>Torque</a> causes or opposes rotation. It is measured in newton meters.<br />2. When the <a class='pjumpToTopic' href='javascript:void(0)' data-chap='9' data-topic='3' data-subtopic='2' data-subsection='0'>force is not perpendicular to the torque</a>, torque is calculated by multiplying the position vector by the force, by the sine of the angle between the position vector and the force.<br />3. <a class='pjumpToTopic' href='javascript:void(0)' data-chap='9' data-topic='3' data-subtopic='3' data-subsection='0'>Net Torque</a> is the sum of all torques acting on an object.",
    "  <b>Vocabulary:</b>  <a class='pjumpToTopic' href='javascript:void(0)' data-chap='9' data-topic='3' data-subtopic='1' data-subsection='0'>torque</a>, <a class='pjumpToTopic' href='javascript:void(0)' data-chap='9' data-topic='3' data-subtopic='3' data-subsection='0'>net torque</a>",
    "  <b>STEM Skills:</b>  <b>    <br />  </b>1. Review <a class='pjumpToTopic' href='javascript:void(0)' data-chap='5' data-topic='0' data-subtopic='1' data-subsection='1'>force</a>.<br />"
